cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for human pose estimation, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the use of multiple cameras and probabilistic graphical models suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques and optimization algorithms suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the use of constraints and reasoning over dependencies suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category.
